 <subsection xml:id="expressions">
    <title>Expressions</title>
    <p>In Python, an expression is a combination of values, variables, operators, and function calls that evaluates to a value. For example, the expression <code>2 + 3</code> evaluates to the value <code>5</code>.</p>
    <p>Expressions can be used in various contexts, such as in assignments, function calls, and control flow statements. For example:</p>
    <program language="python">
      <code>
x = 2 + 3
print(x)
      </code>
    </program>
    <p>In this example, the expression <code>2 + 3</code> is evaluated and assigned to the variable <code>x</code>, which is then printed.</p>
  </subsection>

